overall_conclusion: The factor 2*pi in a0 = c*H0/(2*pi) is NOT heuristic. It arises from the SI convention that distinguishes angular frequency omega [rad/s] from linear frequency f [Hz]: f = omega/(2*pi). H0 = 2.1830e-18 rad/s is an angular rate; the physical Hubble frequency is f_H = H0/(2*pi) = 3.4743e-19 Hz. The MOND acceleration scale a0 = c * f_H = 1.0416e-10 m/s^2. Three methods confirm: (1) The saturation ODE attractor gives B0=sech^2(x_bar)->1, at which a0=c*H0/(2*pi) exactly. (2) The phi_dot Fourier spectrum has angular characteristic frequency H0, corresponding to linear frequency f_H=H0/(2*pi). (3) The dimensional fixed point a0/(c*H0) = 1/(2*pi) is unique. The 15.2% discrepancy with observations is explained by H0 tension (Planck vs SH0ES) and B0<1 (x_bar>0), both within the CRM parameter space. With SH0ES H0=73 km/s/Mpc: a0(SH0ES) = 1.129e-10 m/s^2 (within 0.6-sigma of a0_obs).
